    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2005-09-26</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2005-10-07T18:18:33Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Amends the federal judicial code to require the U.S. Supreme Court to permit television coverage of all open sessions of the Court unless the justices decide, by majority vote, that such coverage in a particular case would violate the due process rights of one or more of the parties before the Court.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>80</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2006-03-30</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Reported to Senate without amendment</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-04-26T21:37:59Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>(This measure has not been amended since it was introduced. The summary of that version is repeated here.)</b></p><p>Amends the federal judicial code to require the U.S. Supreme Court to permit television coverage of all open sessions of the Court unless the justices decide, by majority vote, that such coverage in a particular case would violate the due process rights of one or more of the parties before the Court.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
